node.title: Police arrest man over disappearance of missing campers Russell Hill and Carol Clay
node.alt: A composite image of a man outside and a woman holding a glass of wine at a restaurant
node.description: Detectives are interviewing a 55-year-old Caroline Springs man over the disappearance of campers Russell Hill and Carol Clay in Victoria's remote north-east more than a year ago.
node.content: ["Police have arrested a man over the disappearance of campers Russell Hill and Carol Clay.", "In a statement, Victoria Police said detectives arrested the 55-year-old Caroline Springs man about 5:30pm on Monday and were interviewing him this morning.", "\"The investigation into the matter remains ongoing and further information will be released when operationally appropriate to do so,\" police said.", "Detectives have made repeated appeals for information since Mr Hill and Ms Clay disappeared while camping in the remote Wonnangatta Valley in north-eastern Victoria in March last year.", "The pair were last heard from on March 20, 2020, and police later found their burnt-out campsite and vehicle.", "Mr Hill was a regular camper in the area knew the 4WD path into the region known as Zeka Spur Track well, having helped build it decades earlier as a contract logger.", "Police said hundreds of people across the state had provided information or assistance to the investigation.", "More to come."]
